## What issue is being fixed?

### Enter the issue address

https://github.com/AdguardTeam/AdguardFilters/issues/198767

### Add your comment and screenshots

1. Your comment

We never have catched up with their update cycle. We have to try aggressive regex rule(s) that will be injected to some benign sites too, hence made `prevent-window-open` more specific. I'd not even `example.*##.ad` can be applied to benign sites too. I suspect `[$domain=/^filemoon-.*\.xyz/]` is obsolete now. As commented in Slack, it looks `{n,m}` is incompatible, but I meant `{5,8}` with the rules.

